answers.body_markdown:
As [cybersam](https://stackoverflow.com/users/974731/cybersam) pointed out, Bolt connector should be opened on embedded instance. This page of documentation shows how to do it:
https://neo4j.com/docs/java-reference/current/java-embedded/bolt/

1. Add neo4j-bolt dependency to pom.xml:
```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
	&lt;groupId&gt;org.neo4j&lt;/groupId&gt;
	&lt;artifactId&gt;neo4j-bolt&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	&lt;version&gt;5.10.0&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```
2. To `DatabaseManagementService` object creation add lines configuring `BoltConnector`:
```java
DatabaseManagementService managementService = new 
			DatabaseManagementServiceBuilder(new File(&quot;target/mydb&quot;).toPath())
				.setConfig(GraphDatabaseSettings.transaction_timeout, Duration.ofSeconds( 60 ) )
				.setConfig( BoltConnector.enabled, true )
    			.setConfig( BoltConnector.listen_address, new SocketAddress( &quot;localhost&quot;, 7687 ) )
				.build();
```

P.S. Same question, more detailed answer: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/77571107/spring-boot-embedded-neo4j-for-demo-purposes

